                    <msContents class="lemmatic">
                        <summary>
                            This is <persName ref="viaf.org/viaf/19690624">Ḥunayn ibn Ishaq</persName>'s Translation of Galen's commentary on the Hippocratic Aphorisms.
                            It lacks the whole of book 1 and the first few folios of book 2; it starts from a middle of comm. on lemma ii. 1. The beginning of each Book is as follows:
                            Bk3: 28a; Bk4: 51a; Bk5: 85a; Bk6: 111a; Bk7: 138b.
                        </summary>  
                           
